
// This Hyperlambda code snippet uses the [add] slot to dynamically append nodes from two different sources, [template1] and [template2], into the [fields] node under the [form] node. The [get-nodes] slot retrieves all child nodes from both [template1] and [template2], and the [add] slot appends these nodes into the [fields] node's children collection. This allows for combining multiple node structures into a single destination node.
add:x:@.form/*/fields
   get-nodes:x:@.template1/*
   get-nodes:x:@.template2/*
